ROW.CompanyDescription: From initial data production, to storage, and to destruction, each stage of the data lifecycle presents unique challenges for those who create, access, organize and manage electronic data. Other challenges - such as data loss or other disasters - cannot be anticipated. Kroll Ontrack (then called Ontrack Data International) began providing data recovery services in 1987. Kroll Ontrack has also expanded its number of data recovery locations - from a single lab in Eden Prairie, Minnesota in 1987 to more than 30 locations worldwide today. ROW.RecordNotes: Established in 1925, US Federal Credit Union is Minnesota's oldest financial cooperative. Among our founders is credit union pioneer Thomas W. Doig, who helped establish over 1,000 credit unions during his lifetime. Today, we are one of the largest and most respected credit unions in the nation. We have a long history of meeting member needs while earning exceptional ratings for financial stability and safety. Throughout the years, we've been careful to preserve this dedication to our member-owners' financial well-being. Guided by our volunteer board of directors, we will continue our mission of member service for many years to come.

ROW.RecordNotes: TruStone Financial Federal Credit Union began with a group of eight Minneapolis teachers who decided the best way to have financial security was to help each other. Our Certificate of Organization was applied for on June 18, 1939. On September 21, 1939 TruStone Financial opened for business. Membership grew slowly in the early years. From 1939 to 1949, the first 100 members joined with assets of $15,000. In the next ten years membership grew to 1,000 with $500,000 in assets. Today, TruStone Financial serves the financial needs of over 58,000 members with assets of more than $600,000,000.

ROW.RecordNotes: SharePoint Credit Union was established in 1933 by a group of Red Owl employees who pooled their money because they knew that the value of their funds would be greater if joined together. Over seventy years later, SharePoint Credit Union continues to celebrate that basic principle with every financial product, every service, every single thing we do for our Members. Together, we are greater. And as a credit union, the money saved and earned is returned to our Members in the form of better rates. Our mission is to provide preferred financial services at highly competitive rates, with a personal touch, which will enhance our Members' financial well-being. In fact, our service is what differentiates us from banks and other financial institutions.

ROW.RecordNotes: For 75 years, the Minnco Credit Union has provided the people of East Central Minnesota with good financial products and services available at the lowest possible cost. Having grown to more than 21,000 members, the Minnco Credit Union is preserving its rich tradition by continuing to provide our members with the products they need to meet the demands of today's hectic lifestyles. Today, Minnco Credit Union members have easy access to four branch locations. In addition to our original site in downtown Cambridge, MN, we have an office in Isanti, Cambridge Cub Food store, North Branch and Andover. The Cub Branch offers added convenience of evening and weekend hours. This branch is open from 10:00 A.M. to 7:00 P.M. on Monday - Saturday and from 10:00 A.M. to 4:00 P.M. on Sundays. But even when the convenient locations and hours do not fit busy schedules, members have access to a surcharge free ATM at each location.

ROW.RecordNotes: Chartered by the State of Minnesota as Farmers Union Employees' Credit Union, Heartland Credit Union officially opened for business on January 3, 1939. Back in those days it took just six or seven members to charter a credit union. W.S. Freeman, Joyce Hanson, J.L. Kelly, Felix Mackey, Harvey Norby, Verne Robinson, and Adam Vierling each bought one share for $5 at an organizational meeting held December 3, 1938. In early 2004 Heartland Credit Union's charter was expanded to serve anyone who lives, works, worships, volunteers or attends school in Dakota County. Today Heartland Credit Union serves over 8,800 members with assets exceeding $82 million.

ROW.RecordNotes: In 1954, a group of Red Wing Shoe Company employees decided to form a cooperative from which they could save and borrow at reasonable rates. The Red Wing Shoe Company Employees Credit Union began operation on June 1, 1954 in Plant 1 of the Red Wing Shoe Company, operated by member/volunteers. Professional staff was hired as the credit union grew, but the office remained within Plant 1 until August 1985 when it relocated to the Armory Center. In 1987 the credit union expanded its charter to allow employees of companies other than the Red Wing Shoe Company to join. The St. James Hotel and S. B. Foot Tanning Company were the first of many local employers who have since joined our field of membership.
